## Decision ledger

<!-- Closed ticket resolutions are appended here as one-line linked gists. -->

- [Verify Mux Webhook Wiring on Flagg](./verify-mux-webhook-wiring.svx) — receiver verified live on flagg (port 3111; `hooks.joelclaw.com` and the Funnel URL both 401 unsigned probes correctly; API token authenticates and lists real assets), but the dashboard registration likely still points at decommissioning panda and the account can't be confirmed from the machine — spun off [Repoint the Mux Webhook Registration and Verify the Account](./repoint-mux-webhook-registration.svx).
- [Repoint the Mux Webhook Registration and Verify the Account](./repoint-mux-webhook-registration.svx) — done same day: Joel disabled the panda registration and registered the joelclaw endpoint; new per-endpoint secret rotated into agent-secrets, worker bounced, and a synthetic signed `video.asset.ready` delivered `200` through `https://hooks.joelclaw.com/webhooks/mux` into Inngest (tampered control got `401`). Mux webhook plumbing is fully live for phase 1.
- [Decide the Originals Archive and TTL Cleanup](./decide-originals-archive-ttl.svx) — Garage bucket on three-body; publish copies (never moves) the source; 90-day TTL enforced by an Inngest cron sweep whose delete gate checks live that the Mux asset is `ready` AND has a progressive rendition; phase 1 must record archive key + checksum on the video record.
- [Audit Course-Builder's Video Pipeline for the Yoink](./audit-course-builder-video-pipeline.svx) — yoink the choreography, rework the implementation: `static_renditions` replaces deprecated `mp4_support`, rendition readiness is a separate webhook state, course-builder's Deepgram callback is unauthenticated (ours must not be), skip the `ContentResource.fields` bag. Full map: [yoink audit](./docs/course-builder-video-yoink-audit.svx).
- [Scaffold joelclaw-video and the System-Bus Consumption Seam](./scaffold-joelclaw-video-package-seam.svx) — repo live at `~/Code/joelhooks/joelclaw-video` (jj colocated), package `joelclaw-video` exports `createVideoFunctions(inngest)` with inngest as peer dep, consumed via pnpm `link:`; hello function registered in system-bus, tsc/tests green; `link:`-in-k8s-image caveat recorded for deploy time.
- [Model the Video Resource in Local Convex](./model-video-resource-in-convex.svx) — a `contentResources` row (`type: "videoResource"`, zero schema migration, zero new indexes — `passthrough` carries `resourceId = video:<shareSlug>`); course-builder's field set plus lifecycle/visibility axes, shareSlug + vanityAlias, publishedBy attribution, and the archive contract; draft↔published reversible, delete = Convex tombstone + hard-delete Mux and Garage. Unfolded [Charter joelclaw-api](./charter-joelclaw-api.svx) (the write path) and [Design the Shortlink System](./design-shortlink-system.svx) (vanity aliases ride it).
- [Charter joelclaw-api](./charter-joelclaw-api.svx) — the strangler: standalone repo, tailnet-only Bun+Hono on flagg, Effect HttpApi contract-first (MCP/CLI derive later), XState v5 general pattern, ultracite-ox + tsgo toolchain, service-token auth with `actor` attribution, full Convex custody transferred before phase 1, `.agent_sources` archives mandatory. Unfolded [Scaffold joelclaw-api](./scaffold-joelclaw-api.svx) and [Transfer Convex Custody to joelclaw-api](./transfer-convex-custody.svx); phase 1 now blocks on the transfer.
- [Scaffold joelclaw-api](./scaffold-joelclaw-api.svx) — live at `~/Code/joelhooks/joelclaw-api`, health on :4200; tsgo + ultracite-ox work as chartered (Joel was right about the ox presets); `effect-smol` doesn't exist on npm (`effect@4.0.0-beta.98` is v4), HttpApi isn't in the beta (Schema+Hono, explicitly temporary) — all in the repo's DECISIONS.md.
- [Make Agent Webhook Streaming Work for Mux Events](./make-agent-webhook-streaming-work-for-mux.svx) — generic dispatcher live-verified (`joelclaw webhook subscribe mux asset.ready --stream` prints real events); registered host+cluster; deepgram is one line later. Side discovery: the host registry sync had been silently broken by a JS `??` in `voice-call-judge.ts`'s CEL idempotency expression (another session's uncommitted work — fixed in place, rides their commit); until that fix NO new function was reaching the Inngest server.
- [Transfer Convex Custody to joelclaw-api](./transfer-convex-custody.svx) — done, all four readbacks pass (`d2466320`): joelclaw-api owns convex/ and deploys :3210; apps/web reads via `link:`. Surfaced a live collision — call telemetry in Better Auth's `sessions` table, written by `apps/live-dashboard/convex/calls.ts` (a second deployer of the same backend) — accommodated with a temporary `v.union`, retirement chartered in [Separate Call Telemetry from the Sessions Table](./separate-call-telemetry-from-sessions.svx).
- [Build Phase 1: File Pointer to Mux Asset](./build-file-to-mux-phase-one.svx) — **LIVE 2026-07-14**: `video/publish.requested` → Garage archive → Mux (asset + progressive rendition) → Convex `ready` via joelclaw-api → published/unlisted, Slack pong delivered. Checksum-idempotent across four debug attempts (one record). Battle scars fixed in place: aws-sdk-hangs-under-Bun (→ Bun.S3Client), write-returns-0 (→ readback verify), archive validator size, port 4200 vite collision (api → :4242). Owed: joelclaw-api LaunchAgent; duration/resolution webhook mapping.
- **E2E receipt (not a ticket):** [manual agent-driven Mux publish run](./docs/e2e-mux-manual-run-2026-07-13.svx) — a 12 s ffmpeg clip went file → direct upload → asset ready → progressive `highest.mp4`, with live webhooks verified through hooks.joelclaw.com into Inngest and four public URLs 200-checked, entirely from agent tools. Surfaced [Make Agent Webhook Streaming Work for Mux Events](./make-agent-webhook-streaming-work-for-mux.svx) (session subscriptions only dispatch github events today).

## Not yet specified

- **Arbitrary pointers beyond a flagg filesystem path** — remote URLs, files on blaine/panda, NAS paths, browser uploads. Phase 1 is flagg-local; the pointer taxonomy sharpens once the pipeline exists.
- **Transcript display on the watch page** — the pipeline side graduated to [Port the Deepgram Transcript Flow](./port-deepgram-transcript-flow.svx); how transcripts render/share on the watch page waits on the watch-page charting.
- **Privacy enforcement on playback** — Mux signed playback policies for private/unlisted videos vs public-policy-plus-obscure-slug; waits on the Convex model and watch page.
- **Announce/share flow** — publishing pings Joel (Discord DM with the watch URL) or posts where the agent was asked; shape follows the agent-surface decision.

## Out of scope

- **Recording capture tooling** — the Loom-replacement *recorder* (screen/cam capture) is its own future effort; this map starts at "a video file exists."
- **Comments, view analytics, viewer identity** on the watch page — Loom features beyond publish-and-share.
- **Migrating egghead/badass-courses production video** — this pipeline is personal infrastructure, not a course-builder replacement.
- **Strangling anything beyond the video pilot** — joelclaw-api's later bites (webhook gateway, Inngest fns, apps/web logic, CLI internals) sit past this brief's finish line; they belong to a future joelclaw-api brief, each bite its own decision.
